Roles & Responsibilities
HR Executive | Construction Industry | Payroll | Times Software | HRIS AMS | Ubi

Working days: Mon to Fri - 8.30 to 5.30 pm
1 Sat - 8.30 to 12.30
Location: Ubi
Salary: $2,800 - $3,500

Requirements:
Candidate must possess at least a Diploma, Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma, Bachelor's Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree, Human Resource Management or equivalent.
Required skill(s): Times software, HRIS AMS software
At least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.
Responsibilities
Work with line managers on manpower requirements, employee relations issues, compensation and benefits matter, HR initiatives, and other HR matters;
Administration of workmen compensation, MOM reporting, insurance claim, etc;
Ensure that HR policies and practices are in compliance with prevailing statutory regulations;
Handle onboarding and orientation of new hires, and exit interview;
Identify training and development needs of employees and propose training programs;
Work pass applications, renewals and cancellation;
Ensure timely update of employees’ database, proper filing system and smooth office administration;
Handle payroll;
Other ad-hoc duties as assigned

